nt-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-eGPXGI hfOvrX pf-151_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-152_ pf-text-1"><strong>Urgent care</strong> - Immediate healthcare services are required for conditions that are not life-threatening but require prompt attention.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-154_ pf-text-1"><strong>Emergency care </strong>- Immediate medical intervention necessary for critical or life-threatening conditions.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-156_ pf-text-1"><strong>Policies </strong>- Official guidelines and principles healthcare organisations or regulatory bodies establish to govern care delivery.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-158_ pf-text-1"><strong>Procedures</strong> - Detailed steps and protocols outlining how to implement policies effectively.</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-jrQzAO jIEVBe pf-160_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gIDmLj bESFPC pf-161_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-hmjpVf IvCUC pf-162_ pf-heading-1-h3">Relevant legislation, regulations, and best practices</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/ComplyPlus_Leading_the_Way_in_Patient_Safety_Guidelines_for_Urgent_Care_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1712920132" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/ComplyPlus_Leading_the_Way_in_Patient_Safety_Guidelines_for_Urgent_Care_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1712920132 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/ComplyPlus_Leading_the_Way_in_Patient_Safety_Guidelines_for_Urgent_Care_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_1500x.jpg?v=1712920132 1280w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/ComplyPlus_Leading_the_Way_in_Patient_Safety_Guidelines_for_Urgent_Care_-_The_Mandatory_Traini